<T>__Basics__</T>
Users can use the tower commands to enter Scroll data for the Tower of Doom,
then display it for easy viewing. **Each Tower is specific to the channel it is in**.
<T>__Entering Data__</T>
To enter data, use the `/edit_tower_floor` command. Shortened names or aliases can be used.

<T>__Displaying Data__</T>
To display all the data, simply use the `/show_tower_data` command.
For a selection of floors, ranging from _lower_ to _upper_, use `/show_tower_data range=<lower>-<upper>`, e.g. `/show_tower_data range=20-30`.

<T>__Clearing Data__</T>
To clear the tower data, simply use the `/clear_tower_data` command with no arguments.

<T>__Importing from Taran's DoomMap__</T>
`/import_tower_from_taran <map name>`

<T>__Configuration__</T>
To show the current configuration, use `/show_tower_config`.
`/set_tower_config_option` to edit the options, and `/set_tower_config_alias` to set room and scroll aliases.

